        17 September 2021 - 23 September 2021

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        I saw some comments from yesterday about how people are wondering what happened to my weekly chart reviews.

        Honestly, I just don’t have the same level of motivation for them that I used to, especially now that I have a full-time job & that’s obviously my main focus now! It’s not even about the comments section either, but talking about the highlights of the Top 40 every seven days in 2021 is nowhere near as exciting as it used to be in comparison to previous years, even since 2016 when I first started commenting here!

        I also feel that the singles chart has lost a lot of meaning lately, with ACR stopping older smashes from reaching their full potential & the three songs rules holding back some really popular fan favourites on an album from even charting at all (besides, in some cases, the hits that do chart aren’t even “singles” to begin with).

        That being said, I understand that a lot of people appreciated the discussions that came out of my reviews & that they even introduced a few people to this forum!

        Therefore, while I doubt that they’re going to happen every single week (& not necessarily on a Friday night either), I will start posting my traffic light reviews again when the chart next updates. :)

        i’m bored so i’m gonna do a traffic light-style chart review.

        🔴 (negative)
        1) yeah, we all knew this was coming, but shivers is number 1. i can’t put into words how much i hate this song. we waited 11 long weeks just for ed to knock himself off the top.
        2) way too $exy debuted. certified lover boy is growing on me a bit, but this song won’t.
        3) abba absolutely crashed this week with their two songs... those songs may sound kinda dated but i’m still sad about them crashing.
        4) oh yeah, remember got put onto acr soon. i may hate edm as a genre, but this is honestly one of the best edm songs we’ve had all year and it’s not even close.
        5) continued gains for if you really love me and my heart goes.
        6) kanye crashed again this week, with off the grid and jail out of the top 40. why.

        🟠 (mixed)
        1) obsessed with you gets a top 5 debut! i weirdly really like the song and i want to see more of this kind of drill, but i feel like pinkpantheress should’ve got into the top 20 with just for me before he sampled her song.
        2) visiting hours is back in the top 20. nothing else to say.
        3) 24/5 is honestly mimi webb’s strongest single to date. it’s nothing revolutionary, but mimi’s vocals are at their strongest in this song.
